==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*swoganan''.  Cognate with Old Saxon [[swogan#Old Saxon|swōgan]] ‘rustle’, Gothic [[𐌲𐌰𐍃𐍅𐍉𐌲𐌾𐌰𐌽]] ‘sigh’.

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ˈswo:ɣɑn/}}

===Verb===
{{Latinx|'''swōgan'''}} (class VII strong)

# to [[resound]], [[sound]]

===Descendants===
*English: [[sough]]

